# Improved
To be honest, one of my weaknesses is that I tend to be introverted. Since I was young, I often felt nervous speaking in front of large groups of people, and this sometimes affected my academic performance.
A few years ago, during my second year at university, I participated in a group project where we had to give a presentation on social issue. I was choosen to present in front of the lecturer and many other students. Although I felt very nervous, I realized that I needed to overcome this fear.
To improve, I started practicing public speaking in front of a mirror and searched online for tips and techniques. With preparation and effort, the presentation went smoothly, and both my team members and lecturer were satisfied with the result.
While I still consider myself naturally introverted, I have learned how to manage my nervousness and communicate more effectively when required.

